-- Turkish Stocks: AFM Film, Denizbank, Ford Otomotiv Active
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-23T14:59:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/turkish-stocks-afm-film-denizbank-shares-move-in-istanbul.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  slumped 2.4 percent to 55,734.34 at the close in Istanbul,
its biggest loss since Jan. 4. Banks led declines, with the
 banking gauge  dropping 3.3 percent on concern  Europe ’s debt
crisis is worsening. Of 100 shares on the main index, 91 fell.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  AFM Uluslararasi Film Produksiyon Ticaret & Sanayi AS (AFMAS) 
, a Turkish cinema operator, rose 2.3 percent to 13.65
liras after owner Esas Holding AS completed the sale of a 40
percent stake in the unit for $39.9 million, or $7.47 a share.  Denizbank AS (DENIZ)  , the unit of  Dexia SA (DEXB)  of Belgium
for which Russia’s  OAO Sberbank (SBER)  and  Qatar National Bank SAQ (QNBK)  are
said to be bidding, rose for a second day. The shares added as
much as 11 percent and closed up 3.2 percent to 17.80 liras, the
highest in more than two years.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)  , the maker of Ford
vehicles in Turkey, rose 0.6 percent to 16.60 liras, the highest
since March 30, after  Ford Motor Co. (F)  was raised to investment
grade by Moody’s Investors Service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
